# MedTrigger — Drag & Drop Workflow Builder

## Overview

Build a **visual node-based workflow builder** (like the Iris reference) where doctors drag nodes from a sidebar onto a canvas and connect them with edges to create automation pipelines. When a trigger event fires, the backend walks the graph and executes each node in sequence.

**Library:** [React Flow](https://reactflow.dev/) — the de-facto React library for node-based UIs. Handles drag-and-drop, edge connections, zooming, panning, and custom node rendering out of the box.

---

## Node Catalogue

### 🔵 TRIGGERS (entry points — every workflow starts with one)

| Node | Description |
|---|---|
| **Lab Results Received** | Fires when any lab result arrives for a patient |
| **Bloodwork Received** | Fires specifically for blood panel results |
| **Imaging Results Ready** | Fires when MRI/CT/X-ray results come in |
| **Appointment Missed** | Fires when a patient no-shows |
| **Patient Due for Labs** | Fires when a patient is overdue for routine labs |
| **Prescription Expiring** | Fires when a patient's Rx is about to run out |
| **New Patient Registered** | Fires when a new patient is added |
| **Follow-Up Due** | Fires when a scheduled follow-up date arrives |
| **Abnormal Result Detected** | Fires when a lab value is flagged abnormal |

### 🟡 CONDITIONS (decision/filter nodes)

| Node | Description |
|---|---|
| **Check Insurance** | Verify coverage before proceeding |
| **Check Patient Age** | Branch by age range (e.g., pediatric vs. adult) |
| **Check Result Values** | Branch on normal vs. abnormal lab values |
| **Check Appointment History** | Has patient visited in last X days? |
| **Check Medication List** | Is patient on a specific medication? |

### 🟢 ACTIONS (do something)

| Node | Description |
|---|---|
| **Call Patient** | Place an outbound Twilio call with a script |
| **Send SMS** | Send a text message to patient |
| **Schedule Appointment** | Auto-book the next available slot |
| **Create Lab Order** | Generate a new lab requisition |
| **Send Notification** | Push an alert to the doctor/staff |
| **Create Referral** | Generate a referral to a specialist |
| **Update Patient Record** | Write a note or update a field |
| **Assign to Staff** | Route a task to a specific staff member |

### ✅ OUTPUTS (end points / logging)

| Node | Description |
|---|---|
| **Log Completion** | Record that the workflow ran successfully |
| **Generate Transcript** | Create a transcript of the call/interaction |
| **Create Report** | Generate a summary report |
| **Send Summary to Doctor** | Notify the doctor with workflow results |

---

## Updated Supabase Schema

```sql
-- Workflows — each saved workflow canvas
CREATE TABLE workflows (
  id UUID DEFAULT gen_random_uuid() PRIMARY KEY,
  doctor_id TEXT NOT NULL,
  name TEXT NOT NULL,
  description TEXT,
  category TEXT DEFAULT 'Ungrouped',
  status TEXT DEFAULT 'DRAFT',        -- 'DRAFT' | 'ENABLED'
  nodes JSONB NOT NULL DEFAULT '[]',  -- React Flow nodes array
  edges JSONB NOT NULL DEFAULT '[]',  -- React Flow edges array
  created_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now(),
  updated_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now()
);

-- Patients (unchanged)
CREATE TABLE patients (
  id UUID DEFAULT gen_random_uuid() PRIMARY KEY,
  name TEXT NOT NULL,
  phone TEXT NOT NULL,
  doctor_id TEXT NOT NULL
);

-- Call Logs / Execution Logs
CREATE TABLE call_logs (
  id UUID DEFAULT gen_random_uuid() PRIMARY KEY,
  workflow_id UUID REFERENCES workflows(id),
  patient_id UUID REFERENCES patients(id),
  trigger_node TEXT,               -- which trigger node started it
  status TEXT DEFAULT 'initiated', -- initiated | running | completed | failed
  outcome TEXT,
  keypress TEXT,
  execution_log JSONB DEFAULT '[]', -- step-by-step log of node executions
  created_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now()
);
```

> [!IMPORTANT]
> Workflows store nodes/edges as **JSONB** — no separate tables needed. React Flow's `toObject()` gives you the exact JSON to save, and `setNodes()`/`setEdges()` restores it.

