## Backend (FastAPI) Endpoints

#### [MODIFY] [endpoints.py](file:///c:/Code/HackCanada/Clarus/backend/app/api/endpoints.py)

| Route | Method | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| `/api/workflows` | `GET` | List all workflows (filter by status/category) |
| `/api/workflows` | `POST` | Save a new workflow (nodes + edges JSON) |
| `/api/workflows/{id}` | `GET` | Get a single workflow |
| `/api/workflows/{id}` | `PUT` | Update workflow (nodes, edges, name, status) |
| `/api/workflows/{id}` | `DELETE` | Delete a workflow |
| `/api/workflows/{id}/execute` | `POST` | Execute a workflow for a given patient |
| `/api/lab-event` | `POST` | Simulate lab event → find matching ENABLED workflows → execute |
| `/api/twilio/voice` | `POST` | TwiML webhook — `<Say>` + `<Gather>` |
| `/api/twilio/gather` | `POST` | Handle patient keypress → update call_log |
| `/api/call-logs` | `GET` | List execution logs |

#### [NEW] [workflow_engine.py](file:///c:/Code/HackCanada/Clarus/backend/app/services/workflow_engine.py)

The core execution engine:
1. Takes a workflow's `nodes[]` and `edges[]`
2. Finds the trigger node (entry point)
3. Walks the graph via edges in topological order
4. For each node, calls the appropriate service (Twilio, Supabase, etc.)
5. Logs each step into `call_logs.execution_log`

